post_text:
Today, DESE hosted a webinar about returning to school in the fall. Understandably, students, parents and staff have a lot of questions about how school districts will navigate COVID-19. The webinar was designed to answer some of those questions. Here are six key takeaways:

1) Students, parents and staff should proceed as if everyone will return to school buildings for instruction in the fall.

2) Because this is an evolving situation, students, parents and staff should always be prepared for the possibility of school closures and remote learning.

3) COVID-19 trends over the summer and guidance from public health officials will dictate how school districts proceed in the fall.

4) All districts, including RGSD, have established new cleaning and building entry procedures to account for COVID-19.

5) All districts, including RGSD, are securing masks and gloves for the fall.

6) All districts, including RGSD, are finalizing comprehensive plans for all possible outcomes. As we get closer to the fall, RGSD will share the relevant plan.

https://dese.mo.gov/

text:
Today, DESE hosted a webinar about returning to school in the fall. Understandably, students, parents and staff have a lot of questions about how school districts will navigate COVID-19. The webinar was designed to answer some of those questions. Here are six key takeaways:

1) Students, parents and staff should proceed as if everyone will return to school buildings for instruction in the fall.

2) Because this is an evolving situation, students, parents and staff should always be prepared for the possibility of school closures and remote learning.

3) COVID-19 trends over the summer and guidance from public health officials will dictate how school districts proceed in the fall.

4) All districts, including RGSD, have established new cleaning and building entry procedures to account for COVID-19.

5) All districts, including RGSD, are securing masks and gloves for the fall.

6) All districts, including RGSD, are finalizing comprehensive plans for all possible outcomes. As we get closer to the fall, RGSD will share the relevant plan.

https://dese.mo.gov/

Breaking News!

MO-ECAC named MSBA Early Childhood Education Program of the Year

(June 11, 2020) - Today, the Missouri School Boards’ Association (MSBA) announced that Michelle Obama Early Childhood Academic Center (MO-ECAC) has been named the 2020 FutureBuilders’ Foundation Early Childhood Education Program of the Year in the large school district category.

MO-ECAC is an innovative early childhood program in Riverview Gardens School District. The academic center serves approximately 245 students. Dr. Lanor Payne has been the director of MO-ECAC for two years.

Dr. Lanor Payne, Director of MO-ECAC, said: “This honor is a testament to the wonderful work of our staff, students and parents. Fostering an environment that fuels the creativity and curiosity of our students is a team effort. We are excited to continue to build on our culture of excellence.”

MO-ECAC will be celebrated at the Missouri School Boards' Association's 2020 Annual Conference in cooperation with the Missouri Association of School Administrators (MASA) in Kansas City on Saturday, September 26.

post_text: As the 2019-2020 school year comes to a close, so will Chaketa Mack-Riddle's time with RGSD. For more than two decades, Chaketa has held key leadership roles in RGSD, including Assistant Principal, Building Principal and Assistant Superintendent of Student Support Services. However, none of those job titles can adequately described her value to RGSD. From connecting our families to resources and organizing events to ensuring the safety of our buildings and developing strategic support plans, Chaketa's leadership skills have been a blessing. Even with her wide-range of responsibilities, Chaketa has always found time to make lasting and impactful connections with our students. She will be greatly missed. Good luck, Chaketa! We wish you the best on your new adventure!

post_text:
*Last Day of School Message*

Dear RGSD Community,

Today, is officially the last day of the 2019-2020 school year. It was a year to remember! Our district faced unprecedented obstacles due to the coronavirus pandemic. In a matter of days, students, parents and staff had to adjust to full-time remote learning. Our district also had to bridge the technology gap in our community and break barriers to basic needs. During the closure, we distributed thousands of assignment packets and healthy meals to our families. We also shared vital information about emergency resources with the community.

This school year was challenging. However, wherever you find challenges, you will also find heroes committed to overcoming those challenges. The teacher who delivered books to a student. The secretary who passed out meals to families. The parent who became a substitute teacher overnight. And the students who remained excited about learning through unthinkable circumstances. Remember the heroes of the 2019-2020 school year.

Thank you all for your hard work this school year!

Dear Riverview Gardens School District Students and Parents:

As the 2019-20 school year comes to a close, many of you have a variety of questions. Key topics include: promotions for students who are moving up grade levels, refunds related to cancelled events and student locker clean out opportunities.

Right now, all RGSD buildings are closed and all district celebrations have been cancelled due to COVID-19. However, as restrictions are lifted, individual schools will share plans and decisions regarding the aforementioned topics. The health of our community will remain the priority. The updates will be shared via RGSD communications channels.

The official last day of school is May 27.

post_text:
The RGHS Class of 2020 Graduation Parade is tomorrow!

Riverview Gardens High School will host a graduation parade for the Class of 2020 on Friday, May 22. The parade begins at 11:00am, and the route goes through the RGHS campus.

The entire Class of 2020 is encouraged to participate. Each student and their guests must attend the parade in one vehicle. Walkers are not allowed to participate.

The drive-thru style event will feature four stops, including cap and gown pick up and an opportunity for each student to walk across a stage.

Visit rgsdmo.org for full details.

shared_text:
Riverview Gardens Education Foundation
May 5 at 11:09 PM ·

It’s Giving Tuesday and your support is still needed.

The Riverview Gardens Education Foundation initiatives include , but not limited to, providing books to the Elementary schools in the Riverview Gardens School District either written by or containing main characters in which the scholars in the district can relate to. We also have our Computers For All Campaign which is a campaign geared towards purchasing Chromebooks for the district to ensure that our scholars have access to technology. We also provide prizes for the District Spelling Bee, as well as fulfill other requests as they arise throughout the district.

These things are all made possible by supporters like you and we appreciate and thank you so much.

post_text: Here is the full schedule of some great the lessons for students during the closure:
shared_text:
Nine Network
April 27 at 3:17 PM ·

Beginning TODAY, we are launching "Teaching in Room 9" two hours of literacy and math instruction for students, Pre-K through fourth grade, will be broadcast weekdays from 12:30–2:30 pm, free of charge on Nine PBS.

The grade-appropriate lessons, taught by committed educators from across our region at home, ensure area kids have access to quality teaching during this academic year shutdown and into the summer, regardless of access to internet or computers. All you need is a pencil and paper.

12:30-1:00 p.m. - Reading, PreK-1st Grade
1:00-1:30 p.m. - Reading, 2nd-4th Grade
1:30-2:00 p.m. - Math, PreK-1st Grade
2:00-2:30 p.m. - Math, 2nd-4th Grade

post_text:
Dear Riverview Gardens School District Community:

All district schools will remain closed through the end of this school year. However, student learning and support services will continue through the last day of school, May 27. This decision was extremely difficult, but it is imperative that we take bold measures to slow the spread of COVID-19 and help save lives in our community.

This decision follows recommendations from local health departments and is in collaboration with government officials. We will continue to follow their guidance as we make decisions on end of year events.

While our school buildings are closed, our commitment to continue providing support for our students, parents, staff and community remains unwavering. Naturally, this decision will spark a variety of questions. Please know we are working to secure all the necessary answers and will share additional updates as soon as possible.

post_text: Happening tomorrow!
text: Happening tomorrow!

post_text:
Cancelled: Student Meal/Assignment Packet Distribution

Effective immediately, our student meal and assignment packet distribution events have been cancelled. As a district, we remain committed to serving the needs of our families; however, recent developments across the country related to the coronavirus pandemic have made the risk associated with continuing distribution events too great. As of today, we are not aware of any direct link to our district. The safety of our community is our top priority.

RGSD will continue to serve its families by sharing assignment and basic needs information through the following communication channels:

Automated phone calls
Emails
www.rgsdmo.org
Facebook @Riverview Gardens School District
Twitter @RGSDNews
Instagram @riverviewgardensschools

post_text: The 2020 Census is right around the corner! Make sure our students count! Every ten years the Census counts everyone in the country. The information is used to determine a variety of important things, including how much funding our community receives for things, such as schools. Households will receive notification to complete the Census by mail, phone or online during the month of March. Census workers will also visit homes. We're counting on you to make sure RGSD counts!
